\cf2 The \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 trafficSourceType\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  dimension represents a prime example of structural divergence between the APIs. In targeted Analytics API queries, these sources are returned as string identifiers, whereas in bulk Reporting API CSVs, they are returned as integers. For instance, the integer \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 1\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  maps to \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 ADVERTISING\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 3\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  to \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 SUBSCRIBER\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  (Browse features), \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 4\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  to \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 YT_CHANNEL\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 5\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  to \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 YT_SEARCH\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 7\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  to \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 RELATED_VIDEO\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 9\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  to \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 EXT_URL\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , and \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 20\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  to \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 END_SCREEN\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 . Analysts must build internal mapping tables to translate these bulk integers into human-readable dashboard formats.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 The Content Format Dimension: creatorContentType\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 A critical non-core dimension for modern YouTube analysis is the \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 creatorContentType\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 . As the platform has expanded beyond traditional video hosting to embrace short-form algorithms and ephemeral content, analyzing aggregate data without filtering by format yields distorted insights. This dimension addresses the fragmentation of video formats on the platform, allowing data to be explicitly filtered or grouped based on the type of media consumed. The possible enumerations for this dimension are:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 VIDEO_ON_DEMAND
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 : Standard, long-form recorded videos, which form the historical baseline of YouTube content.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 SHORTS
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 : Vertical, short-form content typically under 60 seconds, which operates on an entirely distinct algorithmic discovery feed and monetization structure.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 LIVE_STREAM
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 : Real-time broadcast events.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 STORY
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 : Ephemeral content designed for mobile engagement.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf3 \cb4 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 UNSPECIFIED
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 : Unknown media types where the platform cannot conclusively categorize the format.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Using this dimension is paramount for content strategists. For example, a channel owner can execute a query passing \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 dimensions=creatorContentType\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  and \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 metrics=estimatedRevenue\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  to isolate the exact financial performance of their Shorts feed distinct from traditional AdSense revenue generated by long-form VODs.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 The Ecosystem of Metrics: Quantitative Measurement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 Metrics represent the quantitative measurements of user activity, engagement, retention, and financial performance. Like dimensions, metrics are divided between core classifications (which are protected by deprecation policies to prevent sudden breaking changes) and non-core classifications. The nomenclature divide between \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 camelCase\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  and \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 snake_case\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  remains consistent here.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

