\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The introduction of reach metrics (\cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 video_thumbnail_impressions\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 ) in January 2026 bulk reports marked a massive shift for bulk data consumers. Previously, top-of-funnel visibility and the effectiveness of video packaging (thumbnails and titles) could only be evaluated via the Analytics API or Creator Studio. By integrating these metrics into bulk datasets, network owners can now systematically identify underperforming thumbnails across tens of thousands of catalog items programmatically. Furthermore, the \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 engaged_views\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  metric was introduced to bulk reports as part of a June 2025 structural change. As Shorts playbacks evolved, YouTube changed the definition of a "view" for Shorts to count whenever a Short starts to play or loop. The \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 engaged_views\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  metric was added to preserve historical data continuity and reflect the older, stricter watch-time-based methodology.\
