\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Report Typologies and Schemas\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 The breadth of reports available via the Reporting API dictates exactly what data points can be correlated within a data warehouse. The system categorizes reports into standard Bulk Reports (created manually via the \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 jobs.create\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  endpoint) and System-Managed Reports (automatically generated by YouTube for financial auditing).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Standard Channel and Content Owner Reports\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 Due to the June 2025 structural change in how YouTube Shorts views are calculated, the vast majority of standard bulk reports underwent a version increment (e.g., from \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 _a2\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  to \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 _a3\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 ) to formally accommodate the new \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 engaged_views\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  column.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

